<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\c_bloom_crisis\c4501_crisis43_memovira</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>75</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Memovira is fuming, firing off orders like stingcharge bolts. "Forget the teleporters! Strengthen the defenses. Stop this beast at any cost. We have prepared for worse demons than *this*!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>She turns and snaps, "What do *you* want?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about this shunt. Can it help us?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>She waves it away. "I don't know. It rid me of one problem, but only partially, and this is much bigger."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ioxu probably has notes on it in the vault but... No. It's a waste of time. Do something useful instead, like fighting this thing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What defenses does the tower have?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Many. Do you think I wasted my reign without preparing for the Bloom? The teleporters have failed, but there's the overwatch slayers, the barriers, and most importantly the bolt throwers, if we can just get them working."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's no more time for questions. Be useful or be dead. I hardly care which."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the overwatch slayers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the overwatch slayers again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the barriers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the barriers again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the bolt throwers."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me about the bolt throwers again."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>She waves a hand impatiently. "Those spheres around the room. They will shoot at anything that threatens me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There are panels around the tower that will activate barriers in various places. They aren't strong enough to withstand anything like the Bloom, but perhaps they'll slow this thing down."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You are a fool. Use your eyes! Press buttons! Just whatever you do, *hurry*!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"On the observation platforms. Ioxu was building these for use against the Bloom. If they can hurt the Bloom, surely they can hurt this *thing*. But we must get them functioning first. If you happen to be even *half* the nano Ioxu is, look at them now. Even one shot from them is better than none."

Her brow furrows. "Ioxu kept some notes in the vault. Perhaps..." She shakes her head. "No, they'd be useless. The varjellen was insane. His notes more so. We must figure this out on our own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You are wasting time! Look at the bolt throwers themselves for your answer. I don't care if you know *nothing* about the numenera, just do it!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Get your people away from the flames."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Get your people away from the flames."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes... Perhaps you're right." She shouts, "Get away from the flames, you fools! You'll only get yourselves killed."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How about you make yourself useful and get down there with them? I'm sure if you threw your own body on them, it would be more effective."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I will do no such thing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Get your people away from the flames. The Sorrow is slaughtering them!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If you value them at all, order your people away from the flames."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How do we get into the vaults?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We *must* get into the vaults."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You don't. I'll not let you hide while my men are slaughtered out here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You mustn't. You're more useful out here as fodder."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps if I slaughtered you and saved the Sorrow the trouble..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We can find something useful in the vaults. Surely t's worth a try."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If you're so convinced we will lose, then what more can you lose by trying?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You said Ioxu kept notes in there. We can decipher them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well. But *only* his notes, understand? Touch nothing else!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's not a risk I'm willing to take. Now get down there and get this thing out of my tower!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well. But if we survive this, and I find you have touched *anything* of value, you will not soon leave this tower!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>She glowers. "Try it and see."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me how this tower keeps out the Bloom."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>She frowns. "There's a defensive barrier in place, at least that's how I understand it. Under the dais. I don't know all of how it works, but it keeps out the Bloom entirely and discourages other unwelcome visitors as well."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There's a whisperlock protecting what's under the dais. How do I disable it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me how to disable the whisperlock under the dais."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's there for a *reason*. The defensive magic barrier must *not* be removed!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fool! I will do no such thing!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Tell me how to open it, or the Sorrow will be the least of your worries!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I can make the defensive magic stronger, but I have to get access behind that whisperlock."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It's the only way! The Bloom wants the Sorrow out as much as we do."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>She grimaces. Then she whistles a haunting tune and says, "There's your key. But I swear to you, if you try to take down the barrier's magic, I will destroy you before the Sorrow has the chance."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The barrier is all that keeps us alive, fool. I will not risk it!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>She considers for a long moment. Finally she whistles a haunting tune and says, "There's your key. But if you try anything that risks the barrier's magic, I will destroy you before the Sorrow has the chance.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>She hesitates for what feels like an eternity. Finally she whistles a haunting tune. "There's your key. If you're wrong - if the Bloom destroys me as well - I swear not even the gates of Abaddon will keep me from hunting your soul." She looks you up and down. "If your kind even has a soul."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So be it! I have not survived the Bloom these many years only to let it destroy me. Let the Sorrow take me first!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>84</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Ioxu mentions a shunt that can shift a creature's phase or plane. What do you know about this?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>She huffs. "I have it, of course, but it's only useful against small creatures. What good is it against this kind of power?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Very well. At this point I'll try anything."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If we can increase its power, it may be the only thing that saves us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Give it to me, or I'll feed you to the Sorrow myself."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't trust you to save anyone but yourself. The shunt stays with me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>She flinches, though she tries to hide it. "Fine. Take it, for all the good it will do you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're welcome to it *after* I have died."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's all for now. See to your defenses."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>"See to your own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>